1
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:34,980
=Wonder Wall=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,910
=Episode 7=

3
00:02:12,760 --> 00:02:13,160
Hello?

4
00:02:13,760 --> 00:02:15,040
Captain Guo, the suspect confessed.

5
00:02:15,521 --> 00:02:17,281
Alright, got it.
I'll head back right away.

6
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:24,841
I'm off.

7
00:02:35,241 --> 00:02:36,200
Bigfoot.

8
00:02:39,361 --> 00:02:40,401
Bigfoot.

9
00:03:22,961 --> 00:03:24,801
We built this neighborhood.

10
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:26,961
These are all
maintenance pipelines down here.

11
00:03:27,720 --> 00:03:28,640
Besides,

12
00:03:29,640 --> 00:03:31,001
this area has been abandoned.

13
00:03:31,561 --> 00:03:32,720
It won't take long

14
00:03:32,720 --> 00:03:34,081
before we reach beneath the villa.

15
00:03:47,081 --> 00:03:48,241
Something doesn't add up.

16
00:03:50,961 --> 00:03:52,281
We've been digging for a day and a half.

17
00:03:52,720 --> 00:03:54,160
It's like a shot in the dark.

18
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:55,720
Could we have dug
in the wrong direction?

19
00:03:55,961 --> 00:03:56,600
No way.

20
00:03:57,561 --> 00:03:57,961
Bro,

21
00:03:58,640 --> 00:03:59,561
you've gotta trust me on this.

22
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:01,001
My ancestors

23
00:04:01,121 --> 00:04:02,561
served as officers under Cao Cao.

24
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:04,880
My great-grandfather's line
were treasure hunters.

25
00:04:05,121 --> 00:04:06,681
My great-grandmother's
practiced spirit guidance.

26
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:08,320
If the spirits showed the way,
how could it be wrong?

27
00:04:09,401 --> 00:04:11,040
We've never missed a spot.

28
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:11,640
Quit yapping.

29
00:04:11,681 --> 00:04:12,841
Both of you, stop arguing.

30
00:04:14,361 --> 00:04:16,760
I feel something's off.

31
00:04:17,280 --> 00:04:17,960
Impossible.

32
00:04:18,801 --> 00:04:19,840
I sent out the goose.

33
00:04:20,241 --> 00:04:21,280
I lit the lamp too.

34
00:04:21,681 --> 00:04:23,520
We built this place ourselves back then.

35
00:04:23,801 --> 00:04:25,520
So where is north?

36
00:04:26,041 --> 00:04:26,440
North.

37
00:04:27,320 --> 00:04:28,041
Don't move. Don't move.

38
00:04:28,640 --> 00:04:29,121
Don't move.

39
00:04:29,320 --> 00:04:29,960
Turn, turn.

40
00:04:30,161 --> 00:04:30,840
Got it! Got it!

41
00:04:31,121 --> 00:04:31,481
Turn.

42
00:04:31,760 --> 00:04:32,520
Turn, turn.

43
00:04:32,880 --> 00:04:33,801
Yeah, yeah.

44
00:04:34,001 --> 00:04:34,801
Turn, turn.

45
00:04:35,080 --> 00:04:35,721
Turn, turn.

46
00:04:35,921 --> 00:04:36,681
Stop, stop.

47
00:04:36,681 --> 00:04:37,520
Stop, stop.

48
00:04:42,481 --> 00:04:43,041
Right here.

49
00:04:44,080 --> 00:04:44,760
Dig upward.

50
00:04:45,801 --> 00:04:46,681
I'm telling you, this is it.

51
00:05:16,640 --> 00:05:17,320
We were off.

52
00:05:18,161 --> 00:05:19,320
So you finally figured that out?

53
00:05:19,721 --> 00:05:20,760
Wasn't this where you said it was?

54
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:26,400
Upgraded to a luxury sedan, huh?

55
00:05:27,361 --> 00:05:27,880
Oh my.

56
00:05:27,921 --> 00:05:29,161
That's our money right there.

57
00:05:32,640 --> 00:05:33,601
Even the way she walks

58
00:05:33,601 --> 00:05:34,601
is different now.

59
00:05:35,241 --> 00:05:36,320
I don't buy that lottery story.

60
00:05:37,481 --> 00:05:38,080
They definitely took the cash

61
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:39,320
from inside that wall.

62
00:05:40,361 --> 00:05:41,561
We built that wall ourselves. We'd know.

63
00:05:41,640 --> 00:05:42,801
Build the wall over here.

64
00:05:42,840 --> 00:05:44,200
From here to here,

65
00:05:44,241 --> 00:05:45,481
make me a wall with
a hidden compartment.

66
00:05:45,520 --> 00:05:46,601
A compartment this thick

67
00:05:46,601 --> 00:05:47,241
would look terrible.

68
00:05:47,241 --> 00:05:48,161
Who's the designer, you or me?

69
00:05:48,161 --> 00:05:48,921
I'm the one living here.

70
00:05:57,200 --> 00:05:59,200
All these years, we were never wrong.

71
00:05:59,481 --> 00:06:00,880
Hu Deshuai has been plotting all along.

72
00:06:01,840 --> 00:06:03,200
That couple was no different.

73
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:05,921
If Hu Deshuai won't pay us back,

74
00:06:06,440 --> 00:06:07,561
then they will.

75
00:06:08,721 --> 00:06:09,760
At the rate they're spending,

76
00:06:10,440 --> 00:06:11,520
they'll burn through it in no time.

77
00:06:14,280 --> 00:06:15,520
Dig. Keep digging.

78
00:06:47,080 --> 00:06:48,721
Why don't we just sell the villa?

79
00:06:49,561 --> 00:06:50,921
Let's move to another city

80
00:06:52,241 --> 00:06:53,161
and start fresh. School,

81
00:06:53,161 --> 00:06:54,041
job, whatever it takes.

82
00:06:54,760 --> 00:06:56,041
With this much money sitting here,

83
00:06:56,041 --> 00:06:56,921
I can't relax.

84
00:07:14,121 --> 00:07:15,520
Let's move the money first.

85
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:17,280
We'll wait until things blow over.

86
00:07:30,561 --> 00:07:31,241
Open the gate.

87
00:07:33,161 --> 00:07:33,640
What are you here for?

88
00:07:34,241 --> 00:07:34,760
Loading cargo.

89
00:07:35,361 --> 00:07:35,840
Which house?

90
00:07:38,481 --> 00:07:39,760
Unit 505. The owner's surname is Yu.

91
00:07:40,601 --> 00:07:41,361
Come on, sign in here.

92
00:08:06,681 --> 00:08:07,161
Mr. Yu,

93
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:08,760
you need trash removal, right?

94
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:11,041
You sure you don't need a hand?

95
00:08:11,080 --> 00:08:11,601
No. I'm fine.

96
00:08:11,760 --> 00:08:12,681
- I'm fine, really.
- We'll help.

97
00:08:12,681 --> 00:08:13,280
Seriously, this is the last bag.

98
00:08:13,280 --> 00:08:14,121
Thanks, but no need.

99
00:08:14,121 --> 00:08:14,640
It's the last bag.

100
00:08:14,721 --> 00:08:15,481
It's the least I can do.

101
00:08:15,481 --> 00:08:16,001
Alright then, thanks.

102
00:08:16,001 --> 00:08:17,320
Really, no need.
Don't get your clothes dirty.

103
00:08:17,320 --> 00:08:18,400
You've got a lot of trash at your place.

104
00:08:18,481 --> 00:08:19,121
This thing is really heavy.

105
00:08:19,121 --> 00:08:20,080
Alright, alright. Thanks. Thanks.

106
00:08:20,080 --> 00:08:21,001
Where's this being hauled to?

107
00:08:21,161 --> 00:08:21,601
The dump.

108
00:08:22,601 --> 00:08:23,320
Right, it's trash after all.

109
00:08:23,361 --> 00:08:24,400
Go on, get back to work.

110
00:08:24,400 --> 00:08:25,320
Thanks. Thanks.

111
00:08:29,640 --> 00:08:31,080
Well, let me get the car out,

112
00:08:31,080 --> 00:08:31,921
Captain Zhan.

113
00:08:31,960 --> 00:08:32,520
Oh, that's right.

114
00:08:33,441 --> 00:08:34,441
Don't forget the seat belt.

115
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:48,841
The noodles are ready.

116
00:08:55,241 --> 00:08:56,400
The money has to be in Unit 505.

117
00:08:56,520 --> 00:08:57,081
It has to be.

118
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:58,321
Twelve bags

119
00:08:58,481 --> 00:08:59,280
that big?

120
00:08:59,481 --> 00:09:00,441
No trash could fill

121
00:09:00,441 --> 00:09:01,520
twelve bags.

122
00:09:01,601 --> 00:09:02,321
It's definitely the money.

123
00:09:02,560 --> 00:09:03,361
He hauled all of it away.

124
00:09:04,160 --> 00:09:04,920
Relax.

125
00:09:05,560 --> 00:09:06,640
Everything in life

126
00:09:07,040 --> 00:09:08,121
has a bad side,

127
00:09:08,321 --> 00:09:09,841
but it also has a good side.

128
00:09:09,920 --> 00:09:11,201
From where
I'm standing, it's all bad,

129
00:09:11,201 --> 00:09:12,121
and then even worse.

130
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:13,920
We've been searching forever.

131
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:15,400
And didn't we

132
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:16,361
finally find the money?

133
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:18,201
That's the good side.

134
00:09:18,321 --> 00:09:19,760
If you don't know how to
comfort me, just don't,

135
00:09:19,760 --> 00:09:20,201
please.

136
00:09:20,961 --> 00:09:22,321
You're only making me feel worse.

137
00:09:22,601 --> 00:09:23,601
I finally found it,

138
00:09:23,680 --> 00:09:24,841
and it got away right under my nose.

139
00:09:25,520 --> 00:09:27,040
Then we'll just track it down.

140
00:09:27,201 --> 00:09:27,880
How?

141
00:09:28,361 --> 00:09:29,280
Yesterday I got him down

142
00:09:29,280 --> 00:09:30,040
and tried to get his fingerprints.

143
00:09:30,721 --> 00:09:31,920
Then the cops showed up
and ruined everything.

144
00:09:33,040 --> 00:09:34,241
He must've hidden it

145
00:09:34,241 --> 00:09:35,601
somewhere familiar to him.

146
00:09:37,081 --> 00:09:37,920
How many familiar places

147
00:09:38,201 --> 00:09:39,920
can one really have?

148
00:09:43,481 --> 00:09:43,920
We'll follow him.

149
00:10:21,841 --> 00:10:23,201
We gotta move everything
up to the second floor.

150
00:10:29,560 --> 00:10:36,040
(Wenming Souvenir Shop)

151
00:10:40,961 --> 00:10:42,520
Once, I was leading a tour group.

152
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:45,361
We passed a store
selling pearl necklaces.

153
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:48,241
As I walked past the display window,

154
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:50,441
I turned and looked inside.

155
00:10:51,321 --> 00:10:52,880
It startled me.

156
00:10:54,400 --> 00:10:55,880
I saw my own eyes.

157
00:10:55,880 --> 00:10:56,560
They were drooping.

158
00:10:56,760 --> 00:10:58,400
My face and mouth were sagging.

159
00:10:59,441 --> 00:11:00,280
My brows were tightly furrowed.

160
00:11:00,280 --> 00:11:01,841
I looked pretty angry.

161
00:11:03,081 --> 00:11:05,040
The muscles in my face were all tense.

162
00:11:07,321 --> 00:11:08,560
That's when I realized

163
00:11:09,601 --> 00:11:10,961
that was my normal expression.

164
00:11:11,560 --> 00:11:12,640
Maybe for the rest of my life,

165
00:11:13,280 --> 00:11:14,601
this is how I'll look.

166
00:11:16,160 --> 00:11:16,841
At that moment,

167
00:11:16,841 --> 00:11:18,520
I really felt sorry for myself.

168
00:11:21,040 --> 00:11:21,760
I'm the one

169
00:11:21,760 --> 00:11:23,361
who made you this way.

170
00:11:25,201 --> 00:11:27,201
I really can't take it anymore, Yu Ming.

171
00:11:27,601 --> 00:11:29,081
I'm not joking with you.

172
00:11:29,721 --> 00:11:30,361
I know.

173
00:11:32,760 --> 00:11:34,160
I've worked hard all these years.

174
00:11:35,361 --> 00:11:35,920
I've tried my best.

175
00:11:36,880 --> 00:11:38,201
Even though things didn't work out,

176
00:11:38,760 --> 00:11:39,241
I've always

177
00:11:40,601 --> 00:11:42,040
wanted you to be happy,

178
00:11:42,241 --> 00:11:43,361
to enjoy life.

179
00:11:44,880 --> 00:11:45,920
If you still love me,

180
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:48,400
I'll use my whole life
to hold on to you.

181
00:11:49,601 --> 00:11:50,560
If what you love is money,

182
00:11:51,321 --> 00:11:52,481
then take all thirty million.

183
00:11:52,481 --> 00:11:53,160
Every cent.

184
00:11:53,520 --> 00:11:54,400
I don't want any of it.

185
00:11:55,241 --> 00:11:56,481
Consider it my apology

186
00:11:57,441 --> 00:11:58,441
to you for all these years.

187
00:12:00,721 --> 00:12:01,760
Right now, those people out there

188
00:12:01,760 --> 00:12:02,800
all have their eyes

189
00:12:02,800 --> 00:12:03,880
on this money.

190
00:12:04,560 --> 00:12:06,241
But I'll still protect
you quietly, no matter what.

191
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:10,790
(Pang Jiajia)

192
00:12:18,241 --> 00:12:19,081
Look who it is.

193
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:20,680
Pang Jiajia?

194
00:12:21,321 --> 00:12:22,441
She's after the money too.

195
00:12:22,721 --> 00:12:23,280
No way.

196
00:12:23,481 --> 00:12:24,400
Don't say it.

197
00:12:27,361 --> 00:12:27,880
Jia.

198
00:12:29,481 --> 00:12:30,040
Yitong,

199
00:12:30,481 --> 00:12:31,520
it's been a while.

200
00:12:31,880 --> 00:12:32,680
Got time today?

201
00:12:32,841 --> 00:12:33,560
Let's grab a meal together.

202
00:12:34,841 --> 00:12:35,800
Sure. Let's do it.

203
00:12:35,800 --> 00:12:36,640
Pick somewhere nice.

204
00:12:37,560 --> 00:12:39,001
You choose the place.
Message me then.

205
00:12:39,680 --> 00:12:41,280
Class is over.

206
00:12:41,721 --> 00:12:42,321
Teachers,

207
00:12:42,721 --> 00:12:43,001
thank you for all your hard work.

208
00:12:43,001 --> 00:12:43,680
Hello, Principal.

209
00:12:45,001 --> 00:12:45,560
Hello, Ma'am.

210
00:12:47,001 --> 00:12:47,560
Principal.

211
00:12:49,601 --> 00:12:50,040
Principal,

212
00:12:50,560 --> 00:12:51,441
our choir's

213
00:12:51,481 --> 00:12:52,400
about to go to the city

214
00:12:52,400 --> 00:12:53,121
for the competition,

215
00:12:53,520 --> 00:12:54,800
but we still haven't settled
on the costumes.

216
00:12:54,841 --> 00:12:55,601
So...

217
00:12:56,481 --> 00:12:57,640
Wasn't it always

218
00:12:57,640 --> 00:12:58,520
that girl, Nana...

219
00:12:58,800 --> 00:12:59,400
Qian Nana.

220
00:12:59,640 --> 00:13:01,001
Right, right. Qian Nana.

221
00:13:01,001 --> 00:13:02,201
Her father used to sponsor them.

222
00:13:02,241 --> 00:13:03,560
I called her dad.

223
00:13:04,040 --> 00:13:05,760
He said business
hasn't been great this year.

224
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:07,280
Said he'd think about it.

225
00:13:08,361 --> 00:13:09,321
But the school

226
00:13:09,321 --> 00:13:10,640
didn't prepare
any budget for this.

227
00:13:11,121 --> 00:13:12,040
Try to come up with something.

228
00:13:13,800 --> 00:13:14,241
Wait, Principal.

229
00:13:14,800 --> 00:13:15,321
Principal,

230
00:13:15,321 --> 00:13:17,400
I've already tried
every idea I could think of.

231
00:13:18,081 --> 00:13:18,400
It's just...

232
00:13:19,040 --> 00:13:19,841
Well...

233
00:13:22,241 --> 00:13:22,841
Wait, look.

234
00:13:23,201 --> 00:13:24,081
That girl's

235
00:13:24,160 --> 00:13:25,601
in your choir, right?

236
00:13:25,800 --> 00:13:26,400
Her name is...

237
00:13:27,481 --> 00:13:28,121
Yu Wenwen.

238
00:13:28,601 --> 00:13:29,920
That's right, Yu Wenwen.

239
00:13:30,920 --> 00:13:32,361
Ask her father if he can help out.

240
00:13:35,841 --> 00:13:36,520
Prin...

241
00:13:38,920 --> 00:13:41,040
Five, six, seven, and start.

242
00:13:41,481 --> 00:13:45,081
♪Raindrops patter outside the classroom♪

243
00:13:45,361 --> 00:13:48,880
♪Whispering little dreams of their own♪

244
00:13:49,040 --> 00:13:52,400
♪Beauty waits within the seasons♪

245
00:13:52,560 --> 00:13:55,880
♪Then blooms softly, petal by petal♪

246
00:13:56,201 --> 00:13:59,441
♪The world becomes a little clearer♪

247
00:13:59,721 --> 00:14:02,680
♪Birds are singing happily overhead♪

248
00:14:02,880 --> 00:14:05,721
♪Breathing in the scent of springtime♪

249
00:14:06,001 --> 00:14:09,640
♪I quietly write
these moments in my diary♪

250
00:14:09,760 --> 00:14:10,481
Stop, stop, stop.

251
00:14:11,121 --> 00:14:11,520
Nana,

252
00:14:11,560 --> 00:14:13,160
that last line you just sang...

253
00:14:16,841 --> 00:14:18,920
You absolutely can't let it drop there.

254
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:20,040
Lift it higher.

255
00:14:20,241 --> 00:14:21,920
Bring the whole note up. Okay?

256
00:14:24,961 --> 00:14:26,520
Get it? Try it again.

257
00:14:27,001 --> 00:14:29,601
♪I quietly write
these moments in my diary♪

258
00:14:29,760 --> 00:14:30,441
No, no.

259
00:14:30,680 --> 00:14:31,400
What's going on?

260
00:14:31,800 --> 00:14:32,920
It was fine yesterday.

261
00:14:37,160 --> 00:14:37,880
Yu Wenwen,

262
00:14:38,760 --> 00:14:39,800
you try that line.

263
00:14:41,081 --> 00:14:44,040
♪Breathing in the scent of springtime♪

264
00:14:44,201 --> 00:14:47,721
♪I quietly write
these moments in my diary♪

265
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:49,081
Not bad. Alright.

266
00:14:49,400 --> 00:14:51,321
Yu Wenwen, switch places with Nana.

267
00:14:51,441 --> 00:14:52,121
You'll be the lead singer.

268
00:15:01,201 --> 00:15:02,400
What are you standing there for?

269
00:15:04,760 --> 00:15:06,201
In our choir,

270
00:15:06,361 --> 00:15:07,800
every student

271
00:15:07,920 --> 00:15:09,760
and every voice is equally important.

272
00:15:10,241 --> 00:15:11,920
No one's above anyone else.

273
00:15:13,040 --> 00:15:14,280
Yu Wenwen, come down.

274
00:15:14,760 --> 00:15:15,680
Nana, move to the back row.

275
00:15:17,680 --> 00:15:19,601
Come on! Switch places.

276
00:15:20,601 --> 00:15:23,001
We lost the last competition

277
00:15:23,001 --> 00:15:24,040
and came in second.

278
00:15:24,361 --> 00:15:25,721
Everyone calls us the eternal runner-up.

279
00:15:25,721 --> 00:15:26,520
The eternal runner-up!

280
00:15:27,040 --> 00:15:28,160
We can't let that
happen again this year.

281
00:15:29,361 --> 00:15:29,961
Everyone,

282
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:32,040
can we bring home

283
00:15:32,040 --> 00:15:33,121
the championship this year?

284
00:15:33,680 --> 00:15:35,321
Yes!

285
00:15:37,040 --> 00:15:37,601
Nana.

286
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:48,481
The competition is coming up soon.

287
00:15:48,721 --> 00:15:49,400
Everyone needs to

288
00:15:49,400 --> 00:15:50,361
stay focused and energized.

289
00:15:50,481 --> 00:15:51,800
Let's sing it through
once more, alright?

290
00:15:52,601 --> 00:15:54,760
Five, six, seven, and start.

291
00:15:55,520 --> 00:15:59,121
♪We are the blossoms of the spring♪

292
00:15:59,201 --> 00:16:02,680
♪Blooming in our fairest season♪

293
00:16:02,841 --> 00:16:03,400
Good.

294
00:16:03,961 --> 00:16:07,081
♪Our laughter fills the air♪

295
00:16:07,321 --> 00:16:10,361
♪Growing into memories we share♪

296
00:16:10,800 --> 00:16:13,961
♪We are the blossoms of the spring♪

297
00:16:14,121 --> 00:16:15,560
♪Blooming in our fairest season♪

298
00:16:15,560 --> 00:16:17,241
Follow Wenwen's movements.

299
00:16:17,680 --> 00:16:20,520
♪Leaving behind our stories♪

300
00:16:20,760 --> 00:16:24,400
♪As a gift for days to come♪

301
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:25,481
Watch your eyes. Your expression.

302
00:16:27,121 --> 00:16:28,680
That was much better than before.

303
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:30,121
Wenwen, nice job.

304
00:16:30,640 --> 00:16:31,160
Keep it up.

305
00:16:35,001 --> 00:16:35,520
Nana,

306
00:16:35,841 --> 00:16:37,400
don't take the lead
singer thing to heart.

307
00:16:38,040 --> 00:16:39,321
Her dad just won the lottery

308
00:16:39,321 --> 00:16:40,280
and bought a new car.

309
00:16:40,680 --> 00:16:41,760
What's there to be so proud of?

310
00:16:42,121 --> 00:16:43,121
Don't be upset.

311
00:16:44,321 --> 00:16:46,160
Yeah, don't be upset.

312
00:16:46,721 --> 00:16:48,040
I'm not even bothered by her.

313
00:16:48,280 --> 00:16:50,640
Look at her socks. They're red.

314
00:16:51,121 --> 00:16:52,321
Who even wears red socks?

315
00:16:52,721 --> 00:16:53,961
Isn't that tacky?

316
00:16:53,961 --> 00:16:54,760
Red ones?

317
00:16:55,121 --> 00:16:56,081
Is it her zodiac year?

318
00:17:18,520 --> 00:17:19,280
Ready?

319
00:17:21,280 --> 00:17:22,161
As for these sheet music pieces,

320
00:17:22,241 --> 00:17:23,481
don't stop practicing.
Practice every night.

321
00:17:25,280 --> 00:17:26,080
Wenwen, you're back.

322
00:17:26,560 --> 00:17:27,080
Let's rehearse together again

323
00:17:27,080 --> 00:17:28,001
in a little while.

324
00:17:28,441 --> 00:17:28,840
Come on.

325
00:17:44,560 --> 00:17:46,760
♪Crush your polite lies♪

326
00:17:47,280 --> 00:17:50,201
♪Use a look of disdain
my mama make for me♪

327
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:52,080
♪Shatter your fake face♪

328
00:17:52,641 --> 00:17:55,840
♪Use the powerful songs
my mama teach for me♪

329
00:18:00,641 --> 00:18:01,201
Wenwen.

330
00:18:02,320 --> 00:18:02,840
Wenwen.

331
00:18:04,641 --> 00:18:05,641
Yu Wenwen!

332
00:18:17,600 --> 00:18:18,161
Wu Xiaoxuan.

333
00:18:19,320 --> 00:18:19,840
Yu Wenwen.

334
00:18:20,080 --> 00:18:20,560
Your phone.

335
00:18:24,040 --> 00:18:25,001
Keep it down.

336
00:18:32,840 --> 00:18:34,560
♪Work hard and make money♪

337
00:18:34,721 --> 00:18:36,040
♪I want to get rich♪

338
00:18:36,481 --> 00:18:38,241
♪A villa by the sea♪

339
00:18:38,360 --> 00:18:39,641
♪Seafood every day♪

340
00:18:41,360 --> 00:18:42,080
Hello, who's this?

341
00:18:42,721 --> 00:18:43,320
Come pick me up.

342
00:18:43,481 --> 00:18:44,120
Right now.

343
00:18:47,320 --> 00:18:48,600
We're putting together a dinner.

344
00:18:49,481 --> 00:18:50,600
Let's go out to eat tonight.

345
00:18:51,641 --> 00:18:53,600
At the very least,
pick a fancy restaurant.

346
00:18:53,681 --> 00:18:53,961
Alright?

347
00:18:54,280 --> 00:18:55,080
Get a private room.

348
00:18:55,641 --> 00:18:56,721
Order the food, bring out the drinks.

349
00:18:56,721 --> 00:18:58,520
Once everyone's having
a good time, they'll sign anything.

350
00:19:00,520 --> 00:19:01,360
130 million.

351
00:19:02,161 --> 00:19:03,320
The lottery winner.

352
00:19:06,241 --> 00:19:07,201
Didn't you see the news?

353
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:08,560
We're like brothers.

354
00:19:09,161 --> 00:19:10,560
I'm serious. Why would I lie to you?

355
00:19:10,961 --> 00:19:12,360
I paid their property fees.

356
00:19:13,320 --> 00:19:13,721
Yeah.

357
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:15,401
Two thousand.

358
00:19:16,120 --> 00:19:17,080
If you want to pay more,

359
00:19:17,080 --> 00:19:18,161
three thousand works too.

360
00:19:19,441 --> 00:19:20,161
Alright, see you tonight.

361
00:19:23,441 --> 00:19:23,961
Excuse me.

362
00:19:25,520 --> 00:19:26,441
Can I get a fruit platter?

363
00:19:26,441 --> 00:19:27,161
I'm dying of thirst.

364
00:19:27,441 --> 00:19:28,241
Sure, coming right up.

365
00:19:28,241 --> 00:19:28,681
Hurry up.

366
00:19:28,921 --> 00:19:29,241
Okay.

367
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:35,080
Jianjun,

368
00:19:36,560 --> 00:19:37,441
haven't you been looking for investors

369
00:19:37,441 --> 00:19:38,201
for your project?

370
00:19:39,161 --> 00:19:40,280
A top-tier investor.

371
00:19:40,360 --> 00:19:41,161
Mr. Yu.

372
00:19:42,320 --> 00:19:43,320
Didn't you see the news?

373
00:19:43,320 --> 00:19:44,040
The lottery winner

374
00:19:44,040 --> 00:19:44,921
who won 130 million.

375
00:19:45,080 --> 00:19:45,600
I'm meeting him tonight

376
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:46,161
for dinner.

377
00:19:46,800 --> 00:19:47,120
Yeah.

378
00:19:47,760 --> 00:19:48,840
But there's an entry fee.

379
00:19:48,840 --> 00:19:49,961
Two thousand.

380
00:19:51,241 --> 00:19:52,760
Cut the crap.
You don't have 2,000?

381
00:19:54,241 --> 00:19:55,001
Then 1,500 is fine.

382
00:19:56,001 --> 00:19:57,120
You have to come tonight. See you then.

383
00:19:57,520 --> 00:19:58,241
I'll send you the address later.

384
00:19:59,080 --> 00:19:59,441
Okay.

385
00:20:04,520 --> 00:20:05,560
Hey, where's my fruit platter?

386
00:20:22,201 --> 00:20:22,760
Thank you.

387
00:20:22,881 --> 00:20:23,320
You're welcome.

388
00:20:24,001 --> 00:20:25,921
So why did you call?

389
00:20:25,921 --> 00:20:27,161
Are you not feeling well?

390
00:20:28,120 --> 00:20:28,641
Let's go.

391
00:20:29,441 --> 00:20:30,001
Where to?

392
00:20:30,201 --> 00:20:30,961
We're buying socks.

393
00:20:32,520 --> 00:20:33,201
Socks?

394
00:20:34,161 --> 00:20:35,280
I just want to get

395
00:20:35,280 --> 00:20:37,001
a new golf club.

396
00:20:37,681 --> 00:20:38,840
Yeah. You get fresh air

397
00:20:38,840 --> 00:20:40,800
out on the course.

398
00:20:43,401 --> 00:20:44,120
Sounds great.

399
00:20:44,760 --> 00:20:46,320
Why are you buying so many red socks?

400
00:20:46,560 --> 00:20:47,320
Because I like them.

401
00:20:47,600 --> 00:20:48,280
Can't afford them?

402
00:20:49,881 --> 00:20:50,681
Buy the most expensive ones.

403
00:20:51,001 --> 00:20:51,681
Your signal's bad.

404
00:20:51,681 --> 00:20:52,360
Where were we?

405
00:20:53,001 --> 00:20:54,080
I don't play the 18-hole version.

406
00:20:54,080 --> 00:20:55,040
I play the 100-hole version.

407
00:20:55,520 --> 00:20:57,001
Why not? Your golf course is huge.

408
00:20:57,001 --> 00:20:58,520
Just dig 100 holes.

409
00:20:58,520 --> 00:20:59,241
Won't be a problem.

410
00:21:00,241 --> 00:21:01,961
I'm not coming this afternoon.

411
00:21:02,001 --> 00:21:03,600
Not playing mahjong. I'm working out.

412
00:21:04,241 --> 00:21:06,040
I've got 3 personal trainers booked.

413
00:21:06,681 --> 00:21:07,721
Stringing all 3 of them along at once

414
00:21:07,721 --> 00:21:08,921
wouldn't be very nice, right?

415
00:21:09,080 --> 00:21:10,681
Don't worry. Alright, bye.

416
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:13,401
♪Work hard and make money♪

417
00:21:14,161 --> 00:21:15,481
What are you busy with?

418
00:21:15,520 --> 00:21:16,641
You've been on the phone nonstop.

419
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:18,800
This elite networking event

420
00:21:19,080 --> 00:21:20,401
is worth five million a day?

421
00:21:20,600 --> 00:21:22,641
Alright, alright. Send me the location.

422
00:21:22,641 --> 00:21:24,120
I'll be there with my assistant.

423
00:21:25,001 --> 00:21:26,120
Hong Jinkui

424
00:21:26,120 --> 00:21:28,161
invited me to one of those

425
00:21:28,161 --> 00:21:29,840
exclusive elite gatherings.

426
00:21:30,641 --> 00:21:32,161
This is where rich people hang out.

427
00:21:32,760 --> 00:21:33,840
I want to take you along

428
00:21:33,840 --> 00:21:34,840
to broaden your horizons.

429
00:21:35,120 --> 00:21:35,881
But I need you

430
00:21:35,881 --> 00:21:37,161
to play the role of my assistant.

431
00:21:37,961 --> 00:21:38,881
I knew you were a real friend.

432
00:21:39,560 --> 00:21:39,921
See you later.

433
00:21:44,320 --> 00:21:45,280
Why'd you stop?

434
00:21:46,161 --> 00:21:47,080
399 yuan a pair.

435
00:21:47,080 --> 00:21:47,881
Can you afford them?

436
00:21:48,760 --> 00:21:50,080
993? Not a problem at all.

437
00:21:52,481 --> 00:21:53,201
I'll take them all.

438
00:22:01,161 --> 00:22:02,080
So have you decided?

439
00:22:02,080 --> 00:22:03,201
Coming with me or not?

440
00:22:03,641 --> 00:22:04,360
No.

441
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:06,080
Come on. There'll be so many

442
00:22:06,080 --> 00:22:07,201
interesting people there.

443
00:22:07,201 --> 00:22:08,401
Great food and drinks too.

444
00:22:08,441 --> 00:22:09,120
Come with me.

445
00:22:09,120 --> 00:22:09,921
You'll get to see

446
00:22:09,921 --> 00:22:11,481
a whole new world.

447
00:22:11,961 --> 00:22:12,441
I'm here.

448
00:22:12,560 --> 00:22:13,001
Coffee.

449
00:22:13,520 --> 00:22:14,120
When are we going?

450
00:22:14,441 --> 00:22:15,120
I need to go home.

451
00:22:20,320 --> 00:22:21,840
This restaurant is excellent.

452
00:22:22,161 --> 00:22:23,600
Look at this decor.
The atmosphere is great.

453
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:25,161
See those lights? They're all imported.

454
00:22:26,721 --> 00:22:28,080
Let's see what we should order.

455
00:22:28,401 --> 00:22:29,641
The drunken shrimp is good.

456
00:22:29,641 --> 00:22:30,441
The ribs are good too.

457
00:22:30,441 --> 00:22:30,961
Scallops.

458
00:22:31,161 --> 00:22:32,360
Steamed cured chicken
with bamboo shoots.

459
00:22:32,681 --> 00:22:33,600
Everything here is pretty good.

460
00:22:33,641 --> 00:22:34,840
Let's order all of this.

461
00:22:35,441 --> 00:22:36,201
The steaks here are great.

462
00:22:36,241 --> 00:22:37,080
Their steaks'

463
00:22:37,080 --> 00:22:38,161
texture and doneness

464
00:22:38,161 --> 00:22:38,921
are absolutely perfect.

465
00:22:39,201 --> 00:22:40,600
How about we each order one?

466
00:22:43,241 --> 00:22:44,760
You really love the steaks here?

467
00:22:53,760 --> 00:22:54,201
It's delicious.

468
00:22:54,560 --> 00:22:55,600
Listen, Yu Ming's gone

469
00:22:55,921 --> 00:22:56,600
completely wild recently.

470
00:22:57,721 --> 00:22:58,760
Only drinks the expensive stuff.

471
00:22:59,360 --> 00:23:00,800
And when he drinks,
he orders by the case.

472
00:23:01,921 --> 00:23:03,600
A side dish that costs 1,200 a plate,

473
00:23:03,641 --> 00:23:04,760
he orders six at a time.

474
00:23:04,961 --> 00:23:05,961
And he's incredibly stubborn about it.

475
00:23:05,961 --> 00:23:06,881
Nobody can talk him out of it.

476
00:23:07,760 --> 00:23:08,481
Back in the day,

477
00:23:08,481 --> 00:23:09,481
I'd have looked down

478
00:23:10,040 --> 00:23:11,641
on that kind of behavior.

479
00:23:13,481 --> 00:23:14,760
But seeing him do all this,

480
00:23:16,401 --> 00:23:17,600
I actually feel sorry for him.

481
00:23:18,320 --> 00:23:19,320
He's using money

482
00:23:19,320 --> 00:23:20,360
to fill the hole in his heart.

483
00:23:22,001 --> 00:23:22,520
That's true.

484
00:23:23,881 --> 00:23:24,961
Yu Ming is a simple guy.

485
00:23:25,641 --> 00:23:26,641
The more he cares about something,

486
00:23:27,840 --> 00:23:28,481
the more he shows it off.

487
00:23:29,560 --> 00:23:30,600
And the more he shows it off,

488
00:23:31,360 --> 00:23:32,560
the more people get jealous.

489
00:23:33,961 --> 00:23:35,241
Once enough people get jealous,

490
00:23:36,080 --> 00:23:37,080
trouble follows.

491
00:23:39,241 --> 00:23:41,320
Simple? He's not simple. He's foolish.

492
00:23:42,001 --> 00:23:42,600
I'm telling you,

493
00:23:42,600 --> 00:23:43,840
ever since this happened to our family,

494
00:23:44,760 --> 00:23:45,401
people have been

495
00:23:45,681 --> 00:23:47,120
swarming around us.

496
00:23:47,800 --> 00:23:48,961
In the shortest amount of time,

497
00:23:48,961 --> 00:23:49,840
I saw human nature

498
00:23:49,840 --> 00:23:50,721
for what it really is.

499
00:23:53,721 --> 00:23:54,921
When I called you today,

500
00:23:55,681 --> 00:23:56,481
you didn't think

501
00:23:56,520 --> 00:23:57,040
I was one of those people

502
00:23:57,040 --> 00:23:57,961
swarming around you too, did you?

503
00:24:00,641 --> 00:24:01,840
For a moment, I wasn't entirely sure.

504
00:24:01,881 --> 00:24:02,840
But I'm sure now.

505
00:24:09,401 --> 00:24:11,040
I've actually been
worried about you all along.

506
00:24:11,560 --> 00:24:12,280
Worried about what?

507
00:24:12,641 --> 00:24:13,360
That I'd get carried away?

508
00:24:13,560 --> 00:24:14,921
That I'd get even
more carried away than Yu Ming?

509
00:24:16,120 --> 00:24:17,201
There's no hole in my heart.

510
00:24:17,360 --> 00:24:18,641
Fan Meijuan raised me well.

511
00:24:19,681 --> 00:24:20,120
That's true.

512
00:24:21,520 --> 00:24:22,641
I'm not worried anymore.

513
00:24:23,161 --> 00:24:23,760
As long as you two

514
00:24:23,760 --> 00:24:24,520
stay united.

515
00:24:25,840 --> 00:24:26,441
The two of us,

516
00:24:28,001 --> 00:24:29,161
for now, are united.

517
00:24:29,560 --> 00:24:30,681
What other choice do we have?

518
00:24:31,641 --> 00:24:32,520
From the very beginning,

519
00:24:32,520 --> 00:24:33,481
I knew you two would never split up.

520
00:24:33,760 --> 00:24:34,280
Sounds like

521
00:24:34,280 --> 00:24:35,360
you know me so well,

522
00:24:35,360 --> 00:24:36,441
even better than I know myself.

523
00:24:36,800 --> 00:24:37,641
Of course I do.

524
00:24:38,481 --> 00:24:39,201
Wow, it tastes so good.

525
00:24:39,961 --> 00:24:40,921
Sir, two more skewers

526
00:24:40,921 --> 00:24:41,441
of this.

527
00:24:41,881 --> 00:24:42,681
Two more of this.

528
00:24:42,881 --> 00:24:43,280
Sure.

529
00:24:44,760 --> 00:24:45,120
Come on.

530
00:24:45,481 --> 00:24:45,840
Cheers.

531
00:25:10,120 --> 00:25:11,001
Need me to walk you upstairs?

532
00:25:11,320 --> 00:25:11,760
No.

533
00:25:12,040 --> 00:25:13,080
Wouldn't want to keep
you from that dinner.

534
00:25:18,401 --> 00:25:19,080
Ouyang.

535
00:25:20,800 --> 00:25:22,040
Do you even recognize my dad anymore?

536
00:25:40,161 --> 00:25:42,921
As for this 2-million-yuan investment,

537
00:25:43,241 --> 00:25:44,280
I'm not trying to brag,

538
00:25:44,840 --> 00:25:46,120
but to me,

539
00:25:47,040 --> 00:25:48,961
it's like a clipping from my pinky nail.

540
00:25:51,360 --> 00:25:52,360
Let me say a few words.

541
00:25:53,641 --> 00:25:55,320
I started with nothing

542
00:25:55,560 --> 00:25:57,040
and made over 100 million.

543
00:25:57,080 --> 00:25:58,921
I went from a street vendor

544
00:25:59,001 --> 00:26:00,641
to owning a luxury villa.

545
00:26:00,921 --> 00:26:01,520
Back then,

546
00:26:01,840 --> 00:26:02,760
I went through a lot.

547
00:26:02,881 --> 00:26:04,441
I even sold fridge magnets

548
00:26:04,441 --> 00:26:05,120
and facial masks.

549
00:26:05,280 --> 00:26:06,760
But once you succeed, all that hardship

550
00:26:06,881 --> 00:26:09,040
becomes strength and motivation.

551
00:26:10,760 --> 00:26:11,600
Mr. Yu truly has

552
00:26:11,641 --> 00:26:12,320
a wealth of experience.

553
00:26:12,600 --> 00:26:13,280
Grounded and hardworking.

554
00:26:13,760 --> 00:26:14,360
In business,

555
00:26:14,481 --> 00:26:16,080
we should all learn from Mr. Yu.

556
00:26:16,441 --> 00:26:17,360
Exactly, exactly.

557
00:26:17,360 --> 00:26:18,360
Back in the day,

558
00:26:18,760 --> 00:26:20,001
Mr. Yu drank water
next to public restrooms.

559
00:26:20,201 --> 00:26:21,320
He even laid his legs
across railroad tracks.

560
00:26:22,040 --> 00:26:23,401
At times like that,
you've got to have guts.

561
00:26:23,481 --> 00:26:24,080
Right?

562
00:26:24,760 --> 00:26:25,881
That's absolutely true.

563
00:26:25,921 --> 00:26:27,280
Whether you're rich or poor,

564
00:26:27,481 --> 00:26:29,120
as long as you've got
courage, you succeed.

565
00:26:29,161 --> 00:26:29,721
Exactly.

566
00:26:30,641 --> 00:26:32,760
Let's drink to that.

567
00:26:33,600 --> 00:26:34,080
Cheers.

568
00:26:34,080 --> 00:26:34,560
Cheers.

569
00:26:34,560 --> 00:26:36,800
Don't hide behind the flowers.

570
00:26:36,840 --> 00:26:37,800
Come pour some drinks.

571
00:26:37,881 --> 00:26:39,441
No initiative at all.

572
00:26:39,721 --> 00:26:41,520
Come on. Let's pour our own.

573
00:26:41,520 --> 00:26:42,921
Come on. Let's pour our own.

574
00:26:42,961 --> 00:26:44,001
Come on.

575
00:26:44,201 --> 00:26:44,721
Hello?

576
00:26:45,881 --> 00:26:46,881
What's up, Xinlu?

577
00:26:47,401 --> 00:26:48,120
I'm having dinner.

578
00:26:49,441 --> 00:26:50,120
That place called...

579
00:26:50,760 --> 00:26:51,760
Xinwang, right?

580
00:26:52,401 --> 00:26:54,001
Xinwang Seafood. Heshan Room.

581
00:26:54,241 --> 00:26:54,721
Come over.

582
00:26:55,641 --> 00:26:57,280
I'm putting my WeChat QR code here.

583
00:26:57,320 --> 00:26:58,721
Anyone who wants to add me, go ahead.

584
00:27:28,320 --> 00:27:29,161
This coin

585
00:27:29,520 --> 00:27:30,881
was only launched recently.

586
00:27:31,161 --> 00:27:32,560
It's still at a low price.

587
00:27:32,681 --> 00:27:34,280
A lot of people

588
00:27:34,360 --> 00:27:35,360
are going all in on it.

589
00:27:35,481 --> 00:27:36,961
I've got insider information.

590
00:27:37,481 --> 00:27:38,161
This coin

591
00:27:38,800 --> 00:27:39,520
will definitely go up

592
00:27:39,721 --> 00:27:41,520
ten to twenty times

593
00:27:41,560 --> 00:27:42,560
within this month.

594
00:27:43,040 --> 00:27:44,320
Even twenty or thirty times

595
00:27:44,560 --> 00:27:45,921
is totally possible.

596
00:27:45,921 --> 00:27:46,681
That's right. That's right.

597
00:27:46,681 --> 00:27:47,641
Exactly. Exactly.

598
00:27:48,040 --> 00:27:49,600
This coin is definitely going up.

599
00:27:51,520 --> 00:27:52,201
Will you stop drinking?

600
00:27:53,840 --> 00:27:54,441
I'm not...

601
00:27:54,441 --> 00:27:55,881
Will you please stop drinking?

602
00:27:56,201 --> 00:27:56,800
Hey, it's okay.

603
00:27:56,800 --> 00:27:58,001
We're talking business.
We're talking crypto.

604
00:27:58,040 --> 00:27:59,120
Don't worry about me.

605
00:27:59,120 --> 00:28:00,080
Ming.

606
00:28:00,401 --> 00:28:01,441
It's alright.

607
00:28:01,481 --> 00:28:01,921
No problem.

608
00:28:02,600 --> 00:28:04,161
Find a seat anywhere.

609
00:28:04,320 --> 00:28:05,320
Come on, over here.

610
00:28:05,441 --> 00:28:06,201
She's your date?

611
00:28:06,360 --> 00:28:07,641
She's basically my wife's sister.

612
00:28:07,840 --> 00:28:08,441
Your wife's sister?

613
00:28:09,320 --> 00:28:09,800
Now go.

614
00:28:10,441 --> 00:28:11,481
Go keep her company.

615
00:28:11,481 --> 00:28:12,241
Go on.

616
00:28:12,760 --> 00:28:13,441
What are you talking about?

617
00:28:14,800 --> 00:28:15,280
Do you even know

618
00:28:15,280 --> 00:28:16,080
who you are right now?

619
00:28:23,401 --> 00:28:24,681
The young man's had too much to drink.

620
00:28:25,600 --> 00:28:26,360
Let me toast you. Come on.

621
00:28:26,961 --> 00:28:27,961
Don't make him drink anymore.

622
00:28:28,320 --> 00:28:28,840
I'll drink it.

623
00:28:31,161 --> 00:28:32,481
Not bad, girl.

624
00:28:32,600 --> 00:28:34,161
One glass isn't enough.

625
00:28:34,681 --> 00:28:35,241
Ming,

626
00:28:35,241 --> 00:28:36,481
look at the state you're in.

627
00:28:37,320 --> 00:28:38,481
He's got a great sister-in-law.

628
00:28:38,800 --> 00:28:39,881
Since you two are family,

629
00:28:39,881 --> 00:28:40,721
one glass isn't enough.

630
00:28:40,881 --> 00:28:41,800
Come on.

631
00:28:41,800 --> 00:28:42,201
Come on, drink more.

632
00:28:42,201 --> 00:28:43,080
Let's drink together.

633
00:28:43,080 --> 00:28:43,600
Come on.

634
00:28:43,961 --> 00:28:45,040
I'll finish the whole pitcher.

635
00:28:45,201 --> 00:28:46,520
As long as you don't bully Ming,

636
00:28:46,520 --> 00:28:47,481
I'll drink as much as you want.

637
00:28:49,921 --> 00:28:51,201
Yeah! That's the spirit!

638
00:28:51,280 --> 00:28:52,840
She can hold her liquor.

639
00:28:53,560 --> 00:28:54,560
Cheers!

640
00:28:54,600 --> 00:28:55,760
You shouldn't have drunk so much.

641
00:28:55,881 --> 00:28:56,800
Don't throw up on me.

642
00:28:57,241 --> 00:28:58,080
It's been transferred.

643
00:28:58,360 --> 00:28:59,080
I've got Song's.

644
00:28:59,320 --> 00:29:00,600
This is from me. Take a look.

645
00:29:00,921 --> 00:29:01,441
It's been transferred.

646
00:29:01,641 --> 00:29:02,320
Alright, that's Li's.

647
00:29:02,401 --> 00:29:02,961
Check it.

648
00:29:02,961 --> 00:29:04,001
It's been transferred.

649
00:29:04,401 --> 00:29:05,401
Got it, got it.

650
00:29:05,441 --> 00:29:06,201
This... This is from me.

651
00:29:06,241 --> 00:29:07,641
Got it.

652
00:29:08,921 --> 00:29:09,360
Got yours.

653
00:29:10,881 --> 00:29:11,401
Xing,

654
00:29:12,241 --> 00:29:13,481
what's with this 200?

655
00:29:14,080 --> 00:29:15,320
I'm really broke.

656
00:29:16,001 --> 00:29:16,520
What do you mean, broke?

657
00:29:16,520 --> 00:29:17,520
We agreed on 2,000 each.

658
00:29:17,520 --> 00:29:18,641
This is all I've got.

659
00:29:18,800 --> 00:29:19,360
Get lost.

660
00:29:19,360 --> 00:29:20,241
Let me see if I've got anything else.

661
00:29:20,481 --> 00:29:20,961
Let me check.

662
00:29:21,120 --> 00:29:21,921
Don't grab it. Hey.

663
00:29:22,961 --> 00:29:23,401
What's this?

664
00:29:24,120 --> 00:29:24,800
Isn't that money?

665
00:29:25,201 --> 00:29:26,721
My wife gave me that for cigarettes.

666
00:29:26,721 --> 00:29:27,600
Forget about the cigarettes.

667
00:29:28,241 --> 00:29:29,080
Leave me some.

668
00:29:29,080 --> 00:29:30,280
You should cut back on smoking.

669
00:29:30,280 --> 00:29:31,441
Too much smoking gives you lung cancer.

670
00:29:31,481 --> 00:29:31,961
Alright, alright.

671
00:29:32,161 --> 00:29:33,201
That's enough. Everyone head home.

672
00:29:33,800 --> 00:29:34,881
Go home and wait for my call.

673
00:29:35,241 --> 00:29:35,921
Wait for my call.

674
00:29:36,001 --> 00:29:36,641
Once I get good news,

675
00:29:36,681 --> 00:29:37,760
you'll be the first to know.

676
00:29:37,840 --> 00:29:38,280
Alright.

677
00:29:38,280 --> 00:29:38,961
Okay, okay.

678
00:29:45,760 --> 00:29:46,600
What time is it already?

679
00:29:46,600 --> 00:29:47,881
Where's he run off to now?

680
00:29:48,161 --> 00:29:49,520
He's not even answering his phone.

681
00:30:01,280 --> 00:30:01,800
Where's Yu Ming?

682
00:30:02,641 --> 00:30:03,961
He's drunk out of his mind.

683
00:30:05,241 --> 00:30:05,800
Send me the address.

684
00:30:26,881 --> 00:30:27,641
Ming,

685
00:30:27,760 --> 00:30:28,760
are you okay?

686
00:31:26,520 --> 00:31:27,161
Master,

687
00:31:28,040 --> 00:31:28,921
Ming is wasted.

688
00:31:37,881 --> 00:31:38,681
Can you stand up?

689
00:31:40,760 --> 00:31:41,280
Honey.

690
00:31:45,800 --> 00:31:46,760
You're here?

691
00:31:59,600 --> 00:32:00,120
Let's go home.

692
00:32:00,401 --> 00:32:01,040
Sure.

693
00:32:01,921 --> 00:32:02,401
Sure.

694
00:32:02,840 --> 00:32:03,320
Gotta run.

695
00:32:27,280 --> 00:32:31,881
♪Back when I ruled my mountain,
I lived free and carefree♪

696
00:32:32,320 --> 00:32:36,201
♪Surrounded by my monkey kin,
I knew nothing but joy♪

697
00:32:36,520 --> 00:32:37,360
♪I stormed the Underworld♪

698
00:32:37,481 --> 00:32:40,441
♪Crossed names from the Book
of Life and Death at my will♪

699
00:32:40,760 --> 00:32:41,840
♪Now♪

700
00:32:42,080 --> 00:32:44,961
♪No sooner had I slain one evil
than its kin came after me♪

701
00:32:45,080 --> 00:32:47,401
♪Life turns♪

702
00:32:47,520 --> 00:32:48,760
♪Like a wheel without end♪

703
00:32:49,080 --> 00:32:49,881
♪Like a wheel without end♪

704
00:32:50,080 --> 00:32:52,681
♪Like a wheel without end♪

705
00:32:52,921 --> 00:32:57,280
♪It feels like nothing
more than a fleeting dream♪

706
00:32:58,721 --> 00:32:59,800
Where'd you park the car?

707
00:33:16,001 --> 00:33:17,320
There was a designated driver
in the car earlier.

708
00:33:17,320 --> 00:33:18,161
You wouldn't let me talk.

709
00:33:18,201 --> 00:33:19,320
Can I talk now?

710
00:33:19,360 --> 00:33:19,921
I want to say something.

711
00:33:20,080 --> 00:33:21,001
Can you even talk right now?

712
00:33:21,080 --> 00:33:21,600
Sure I can.

713
00:33:21,600 --> 00:33:22,241
Are you sober?

714
00:33:22,320 --> 00:33:23,001
Sure I am.

715
00:33:23,241 --> 00:33:24,080
At first,

716
00:33:24,080 --> 00:33:26,080
when I was drunk,

717
00:33:26,080 --> 00:33:26,800
I was lying

718
00:33:26,800 --> 00:33:28,201
on a man's stomach.

719
00:33:28,241 --> 00:33:30,241
I fell asleep on his stomach.

720
00:33:30,320 --> 00:33:31,120
But when I woke up,

721
00:33:31,120 --> 00:33:32,040
somehow I ended up

722
00:33:32,040 --> 00:33:33,320
on Liu Xinlu's lap.

723
00:33:33,320 --> 00:33:34,600
I have no idea how.

724
00:33:35,520 --> 00:33:36,800
I don't care whose legs

725
00:33:36,800 --> 00:33:38,120
or whose stomach you sleep on.

726
00:33:38,120 --> 00:33:38,921
I know exactly

727
00:33:38,921 --> 00:33:39,721
what kind of person you are.

728
00:33:39,800 --> 00:33:40,800
That's not the issue right now,

729
00:33:40,800 --> 00:33:41,280
Yu Ming.

730
00:33:42,201 --> 00:33:43,201
You've gotten carried away.

731
00:33:43,441 --> 00:33:44,401
Think back

732
00:33:44,481 --> 00:33:45,360
on the things you've been saying lately.

733
00:33:45,360 --> 00:33:45,921
The alcohol you've been drinking.

734
00:33:45,921 --> 00:33:46,721
The things you've been doing.

735
00:33:46,921 --> 00:33:47,760
Do you really think they're appropriate?

736
00:33:47,961 --> 00:33:48,681
No.

737
00:33:48,681 --> 00:33:50,280
I know they're not.

738
00:33:50,360 --> 00:33:51,280
Sometimes, when
the bragging reaches my lips,

739
00:33:51,280 --> 00:33:52,600
I want to hold it back too.

740
00:33:52,600 --> 00:33:53,080
But

741
00:33:53,641 --> 00:33:54,641
it's like it has some kind of magic.

742
00:33:54,641 --> 00:33:55,560
It pries my mouth open

743
00:33:55,560 --> 00:33:57,040
and pops right out.

744
00:33:57,560 --> 00:33:58,961
I regret it too.

745
00:33:59,001 --> 00:34:00,681
Even if it's hard,
you've got to keep it in.

746
00:34:00,840 --> 00:34:02,120
Man, you're a father.

747
00:34:02,201 --> 00:34:03,721
You're the friend
of good friends of yours.

748
00:34:03,760 --> 00:34:05,241
We should at least
try to be decent people.

749
00:34:05,241 --> 00:34:05,760
Can you do that?

750
00:34:06,280 --> 00:34:06,681
Yes.

751
00:34:07,441 --> 00:34:08,600
I won't drink anymore.

752
00:34:09,281 --> 00:34:10,040
I promise you.

753
00:34:10,040 --> 00:34:11,080
And I won't show off anymore.

754
00:34:11,560 --> 00:34:12,160
Can you really do that?

755
00:34:12,200 --> 00:34:13,001
Yes. Yes, I can.

756
00:34:17,881 --> 00:34:19,200
When we left just now,

757
00:34:19,640 --> 00:34:21,120
did you happen to see

758
00:34:21,640 --> 00:34:22,680
a monkey that could sing

759
00:34:22,680 --> 00:34:23,481
sitting on the table?

760
00:34:25,200 --> 00:34:25,720
Did you happen to see

761
00:34:25,720 --> 00:34:26,921
a slap flying toward your face?

762
00:34:27,441 --> 00:34:28,841
I'm not joking.

763
00:34:30,040 --> 00:34:31,040
That was a waste of breath.

764
00:34:31,200 --> 00:34:32,200
Talk to me when you're sober.

765
00:34:35,600 --> 00:34:36,921
I am sober.

766
00:34:41,761 --> 00:34:42,481
Starting tomorrow,

767
00:34:43,160 --> 00:34:44,080
wherever he goes, I go.

768
00:34:44,801 --> 00:34:45,441
I'll stick to him like glue.

769
00:34:46,281 --> 00:34:47,200
We'll see about that.

770
00:34:48,281 --> 00:34:49,321
Let's see how many hideouts

771
00:34:49,321 --> 00:34:49,801
he has.

772
00:34:50,160 --> 00:34:50,841
Exactly.

773
00:34:51,200 --> 00:34:52,881
You keep an eye on that Yu guy.

774
00:34:53,080 --> 00:34:54,200
I'll follow his wife.

775
00:34:55,801 --> 00:34:56,720
If that's how we're doing it,

776
00:34:57,080 --> 00:34:57,961
those 3 idiots

777
00:34:57,961 --> 00:34:58,881
are useless now.

778
00:35:00,600 --> 00:35:01,761
Chun. Ma'am.

779
00:35:02,001 --> 00:35:02,481
You're here.

780
00:35:04,040 --> 00:35:04,720
I'm exhausted.

781
00:35:04,720 --> 00:35:05,080
Ma'am,

782
00:35:05,240 --> 00:35:05,921
make 3 bowls of noodles.

783
00:35:06,200 --> 00:35:06,600
Okay.

784
00:35:10,801 --> 00:35:11,160
Here.

785
00:35:13,560 --> 00:35:14,680
We're almost through.

786
00:35:15,160 --> 00:35:16,120
Based on my ancestors' experience,

787
00:35:16,200 --> 00:35:17,040
three more days at most.

788
00:35:17,120 --> 00:35:17,921
Forget 3 days.

789
00:35:18,001 --> 00:35:18,560
Stop digging.

790
00:35:19,120 --> 00:35:19,961
The money isn't there anymore.

791
00:35:21,040 --> 00:35:21,640
What do you mean?

792
00:35:21,881 --> 00:35:23,160
A truck hauled trash
away from Unit 505 today.

793
00:35:23,361 --> 00:35:24,120
More than a dozen bags.

794
00:35:24,401 --> 00:35:25,080
Each one this big.

795
00:35:25,640 --> 00:35:26,361
It had to be the money.

796
00:35:26,680 --> 00:35:27,200
They moved it.

797
00:35:27,520 --> 00:35:28,801
Then all this digging was for nothing?

798
00:35:28,881 --> 00:35:29,441
For nothing.

799
00:35:29,441 --> 00:35:30,361
You dug too slowly.

800
00:35:30,921 --> 00:35:32,040
Are... Are you sure?

801
00:35:32,080 --> 00:35:32,961
Of course I'm sure.

802
00:35:32,961 --> 00:35:33,640
I watched them haul it away.

803
00:35:33,640 --> 00:35:34,321
Where'd they take it?

804
00:35:34,321 --> 00:35:35,240
How would I know where they took it?

805
00:35:35,240 --> 00:35:35,961
Then why didn't you follow them?

806
00:35:35,961 --> 00:35:36,720
How was I supposed to follow them?

807
00:35:36,720 --> 00:35:37,520
I was in uniform.

808
00:35:37,520 --> 00:35:38,841
You expect me to
tail them out in the open?

809
00:35:38,841 --> 00:35:39,361
You should've told us

810
00:35:39,361 --> 00:35:40,240
so we could follow them.

811
00:35:40,281 --> 00:35:41,040
I'm telling you now.

812
00:35:41,040 --> 00:35:41,720
Then you go follow them.

813
00:35:41,720 --> 00:35:42,600
You're only telling us now.

814
00:35:42,600 --> 00:35:42,961
How are we supposed to follow them?

815
00:35:42,961 --> 00:35:43,680
If I'd told you back then,

816
00:35:43,680 --> 00:35:44,240
would you even have caught up?

817
00:35:44,240 --> 00:35:44,801
If you didn't tell us,

818
00:35:44,801 --> 00:35:45,481
how would we know

819
00:35:45,520 --> 00:35:46,520
we couldn't catch up?

820
00:35:46,520 --> 00:35:47,481
What's wrong with you?

821
00:35:54,961 --> 00:35:55,401
Bro,

822
00:35:56,520 --> 00:35:57,040
what do we do?

823
00:36:00,200 --> 00:36:00,640
Bro.

824
00:36:02,640 --> 00:36:03,001
Bro.

825
00:36:03,001 --> 00:36:04,281
They freeload us every day.

826
00:36:05,160 --> 00:36:06,481
Why did you even argue with them?

827
00:36:06,921 --> 00:36:07,881
What's there to argue about?

828
00:36:11,640 --> 00:36:12,001
Let's go.

829
00:36:13,401 --> 00:36:14,281
We'll eat somewhere else.

830
00:36:15,240 --> 00:36:16,120
You're actually mad?

831
00:36:19,200 --> 00:36:19,560
Come on.

832
00:36:20,001 --> 00:36:20,841
Let's eat somewhere else.

833
00:36:26,640 --> 00:36:27,240
They're gone.

834
00:36:27,761 --> 00:36:28,761
No noodles for them then.

835
00:36:32,200 --> 00:36:33,801
Worked all day and didn't get a penny.

836
00:36:34,001 --> 00:36:34,961
All we did was dig holes.

837
00:36:40,680 --> 00:36:41,961
Stop eating.
Food's all you're ever worried about.

838
00:36:42,001 --> 00:36:42,720
Does that little gadget of yours

839
00:36:42,720 --> 00:36:43,600
even work?

840
00:36:43,801 --> 00:36:44,761
Treasure hunter? Seriously?

841
00:36:44,841 --> 00:36:46,160
At this point, I don't know
if you're the problem

842
00:36:46,160 --> 00:36:47,401
or your great-grandma was.

843
00:36:47,841 --> 00:36:49,321
You can say I'm useless,
but don't talk about my great-grandma.

844
00:36:49,441 --> 00:36:50,921
If your great-grandma was so good,
would we have dug in the wrong spot?

845
00:36:50,921 --> 00:36:51,560
We'd have broken through already.

846
00:36:51,600 --> 00:36:52,281
Alright now.

847
00:36:52,281 --> 00:36:52,921
Enough already.

848
00:37:01,881 --> 00:37:02,160
Bro.

849
00:37:02,160 --> 00:37:03,040
Sir, one bowl of noodles.

850
00:37:03,200 --> 00:37:04,240
When are we leaving tomorrow?

851
00:37:04,720 --> 00:37:05,560
Leaving? Why would we leave?

852
00:37:06,001 --> 00:37:07,240
We haven't gotten the money yet.

853
00:37:07,281 --> 00:37:08,240
Zhan Chun said

854
00:37:08,240 --> 00:37:09,441
they hauled the money away.

855
00:37:09,481 --> 00:37:11,001
Just because Zhan Chun said so,
that makes it true?

856
00:37:11,080 --> 00:37:12,921
He said they hauled away trash.

857
00:37:12,961 --> 00:37:13,961
He just felt there was money inside.

858
00:37:14,001 --> 00:37:14,961
He never opened the bags.

859
00:37:17,200 --> 00:37:17,921
It was just a feeling?

860
00:37:18,921 --> 00:37:20,160
Yeah. Just a feeling.

861
00:37:21,321 --> 00:37:22,801
Those two don't look trustworthy to me.

862
00:37:22,801 --> 00:37:23,401
They seem shady.

863
00:37:23,761 --> 00:37:24,720
If we really leave

864
00:37:24,961 --> 00:37:26,160
and the money's still
in there, then what?

865
00:37:26,401 --> 00:37:26,961
Then what?

866
00:37:32,921 --> 00:37:33,640
I don't buy it.

867
00:37:34,481 --> 00:37:35,080
We're digging again.

868
00:37:39,560 --> 00:37:40,881
I've never missed a rent payment.

869
00:37:41,520 --> 00:37:42,401
Why won't you let me stay?

870
00:37:43,560 --> 00:37:44,680
Listen,

871
00:37:45,361 --> 00:37:46,761
this house belongs to me.

872
00:37:47,200 --> 00:37:49,080
I can rent it to whoever I want.

873
00:37:49,080 --> 00:37:50,200
And if I don't want
to rent it to someone,

874
00:37:50,200 --> 00:37:51,240
then I won't.

875
00:37:51,680 --> 00:37:52,481
Besides, that young lady

876
00:37:52,801 --> 00:37:54,361
is paying 1,000

877
00:37:54,361 --> 00:37:55,080
more than you.

878
00:37:57,200 --> 00:37:58,680
Call Miss Li right now.

879
00:37:58,881 --> 00:37:59,761
Tell her the place is available.

880
00:37:59,761 --> 00:38:01,040
She can sign the lease this afternoon.

881
00:38:01,361 --> 00:38:02,520
What a fool.

882
00:38:04,001 --> 00:38:04,361
What...

883
00:38:05,040 --> 00:38:05,481
What you're doing

884
00:38:05,481 --> 00:38:06,640
is a violation of the rental agreement.

885
00:38:07,961 --> 00:38:09,520
The lease expires this month anyway.

886
00:38:13,640 --> 00:38:14,080
Fine.

887
00:38:14,640 --> 00:38:15,560
Then give me my deposit back.

888
00:38:16,481 --> 00:38:17,361
I'll pack up and leave today.

889
00:38:17,680 --> 00:38:18,600
Your deposit?

890
00:38:18,761 --> 00:38:19,761
Look at this place.

891
00:38:19,761 --> 00:38:20,961
Look what you've done to it.

892
00:38:21,481 --> 00:38:22,281
And you still want your deposit?

893
00:38:22,680 --> 00:38:23,040
I...

894
00:38:23,520 --> 00:38:25,040
The bathroom light is broken.

895
00:38:25,160 --> 00:38:25,761
It doesn't work.

896
00:38:26,520 --> 00:38:27,160
That's 100 yuan.

897
00:38:27,520 --> 00:38:28,720
Wait. That bathroom light

898
00:38:28,720 --> 00:38:29,680
was already broken

899
00:38:29,680 --> 00:38:30,401
when I moved in.

900
00:38:30,640 --> 00:38:31,600
The wiring was bad.

901
00:38:32,080 --> 00:38:33,401
Sometimes it worked,
sometimes it didn't.

902
00:38:33,761 --> 00:38:35,240
But it worked sometimes back then.

903
00:38:35,240 --> 00:38:35,720
Right?

904
00:38:36,321 --> 00:38:36,720
Move aside.

905
00:38:37,560 --> 00:38:38,881
What a fool.

906
00:38:40,481 --> 00:38:41,361
Let me show you.

907
00:38:41,640 --> 00:38:42,600
Right now it's off.

908
00:38:42,961 --> 00:38:43,441
Dark.

909
00:38:43,841 --> 00:38:44,361
Turn it on.

910
00:38:44,600 --> 00:38:45,321
Still dark.

911
00:38:45,520 --> 00:38:46,600
Switch on, switch off.

912
00:38:46,761 --> 00:38:47,520
It's dark both ways.

913
00:38:47,761 --> 00:38:49,120
If it's dark, it doesn't work.

914
00:38:49,321 --> 00:38:50,841
Is charging you 100 yuan unreasonable?

915
00:38:52,801 --> 00:38:53,240
Fine.

916
00:38:53,680 --> 00:38:54,120
Put it on the bill.

917
00:38:59,040 --> 00:39:00,441
Heat lamp depreciation fee, 800.

918
00:39:01,441 --> 00:39:02,560
Eight hundred.

919
00:39:02,560 --> 00:39:04,560
Bathroom ceiling damage

920
00:39:05,120 --> 00:39:05,921
repair fee,

921
00:39:06,560 --> 00:39:07,200
five hundred.

922
00:39:12,481 --> 00:39:14,321
Toilet depreciation fee, 500.

923
00:39:15,281 --> 00:39:17,120
My toilet brush used to be brand new.

924
00:39:17,120 --> 00:39:18,120
Look what you've done to it.

925
00:39:18,680 --> 00:39:19,321
Eighty yuan.

926
00:39:20,640 --> 00:39:22,040
Shower depreciation fee,

927
00:39:22,441 --> 00:39:23,160
eight hundred.

928
00:39:25,481 --> 00:39:26,801
Washing machine depreciation, 500.

929
00:39:28,281 --> 00:39:29,640
Five hundred for the washing machine.

930
00:39:30,881 --> 00:39:32,200
Air conditioner, 800 yuan.

931
00:39:33,881 --> 00:39:35,761
Loose faucet, 150.

932
00:39:36,600 --> 00:39:37,560
150 yuan.

933
00:39:44,001 --> 00:39:45,240
Sofa depreciation, 300.

934
00:39:46,520 --> 00:39:48,441
Three hundred for the sofa.

935
00:39:50,240 --> 00:39:51,080
Peeling paint on the wall,

936
00:39:51,240 --> 00:39:51,801
150 yuan.

937
00:39:52,080 --> 00:39:53,321
150 yuan for the wall.

938
00:39:56,281 --> 00:39:58,001
Add this month's rent,

939
00:39:58,160 --> 00:39:59,040
subtract the deposit,

940
00:39:59,240 --> 00:40:00,761
and the total comes to

941
00:40:00,801 --> 00:40:01,921
6,850 yuan.

942
00:40:02,640 --> 00:40:03,200
Don't you think

943
00:40:03,200 --> 00:40:04,160
this is a bit excessive?

944
00:40:05,520 --> 00:40:06,361
How is it excessive?

945
00:40:06,961 --> 00:40:07,520
Young lady,

946
00:40:07,560 --> 00:40:08,921
everything's clearly written here.

947
00:40:09,120 --> 00:40:10,720
Every item is listed.

948
00:40:10,841 --> 00:40:11,761
We didn't overcharge you.

949
00:40:11,881 --> 00:40:12,640
Pay up.

950
00:40:21,801 --> 00:40:22,520
This is all I have.

951
00:40:22,801 --> 00:40:23,761
What about the rest?

952
00:40:26,761 --> 00:40:27,720
When I get paid next month,

953
00:40:27,720 --> 00:40:28,321
I'll give it to you then.

954
00:40:29,441 --> 00:40:30,600
Who knows where you'll be living

955
00:40:30,600 --> 00:40:31,560
next month?

956
00:40:31,560 --> 00:40:32,720
How am I supposed to find you?

957
00:40:32,761 --> 00:40:33,520
Next month?

958
00:40:33,640 --> 00:40:35,040
Leave your luggage here as collateral.

959
00:40:35,441 --> 00:40:36,001
No.

960
00:40:36,560 --> 00:40:37,720
You're such a fool.

961
00:40:37,801 --> 00:40:39,001
How much is her luggage worth?

962
00:40:41,881 --> 00:40:43,720
That instrument's
valuable though, right?

963
00:40:43,961 --> 00:40:45,120
We'll keep that.

964
00:40:45,200 --> 00:40:45,560
Alright?

965
00:40:45,560 --> 00:40:46,520
- Take the instrument.
- No, not this.

966
00:40:47,881 --> 00:40:48,120
You...

967
00:40:48,240 --> 00:40:48,680
What are you doing?

968
00:40:48,680 --> 00:40:49,441
I'll leave my luggage with you.

969
00:40:49,640 --> 00:40:50,761
Your luggage isn't worth anything.

970
00:40:50,761 --> 00:40:51,441
Give me that now,

971
00:40:51,441 --> 00:40:52,321
or I'm calling the police.

972
00:40:52,441 --> 00:40:53,200
Calling the police?

973
00:40:53,441 --> 00:40:54,921
You owe me rent
and you're calling the police?

974
00:40:56,200 --> 00:40:56,600
Go away.

975
00:41:24,200 --> 00:41:25,080
Then leave the luggage.

976
00:41:34,761 --> 00:41:36,481
♪Work hard and make money♪

977
00:41:36,640 --> 00:41:37,961
♪I want to get rich♪

978
00:41:38,401 --> 00:41:40,160
♪A villa by the sea♪

979
00:41:41,961 --> 00:41:42,881
Who is this?

980
00:41:43,361 --> 00:41:44,680
Hello, is it Mr. Yu?

981
00:41:45,120 --> 00:41:46,120
This is Jiang Xiaoling

982
00:41:46,120 --> 00:41:46,720
from property management.

983
00:41:46,801 --> 00:41:48,080
The pile of stuff outside your door

984
00:41:48,080 --> 00:41:48,841
caught fire.

985
00:41:49,600 --> 00:41:50,321
No idea what's going on

986
00:41:50,321 --> 00:41:50,921
inside the house.

987
00:41:51,040 --> 00:41:52,321
You should come back right away.

988
00:41:52,921 --> 00:41:53,640
I'm on my way.

989
00:42:12,640 --> 00:42:13,481
You should check the stuff

990
00:42:13,481 --> 00:42:14,720
piling outside your house.

991
00:42:14,720 --> 00:42:15,600
Check the damage.

992
00:42:15,801 --> 00:42:17,401
The smoke was huge just now.

993
00:42:20,881 --> 00:42:21,441
Take a look.

994
00:42:21,801 --> 00:42:23,281
How... How did it catch fire?

995
00:42:24,001 --> 00:42:24,720
No idea.

996
00:42:24,801 --> 00:42:26,401
Good thing Captain Zhan
spotted it in time,

997
00:42:26,560 --> 00:42:27,200
or the fire

998
00:42:27,200 --> 00:42:28,321
would've spread into the house.

999
00:42:28,680 --> 00:42:29,160
It was nothing.

1000
00:42:29,640 --> 00:42:30,520
I thought you were having a barbecue,

1001
00:42:30,520 --> 00:42:31,040
Mr. Yu.

1002
00:42:31,321 --> 00:42:32,001
No, no.

1003
00:42:33,321 --> 00:42:34,441
See if anything got damaged.

1004
00:43:05,080 --> 00:43:07,880
(Next Episode)

1005
00:43:08,401 --> 00:43:09,841
(Actor, Guo Jingfei)
Hi, I'm Guo Jingfei.

1006
00:43:09,841 --> 00:43:12,160
(Actor, Guo Jingfei)
I invite you to watch Wonder Wall.

1007
00:43:12,240 --> 00:43:13,640
Stay away from my bro.

1008
00:43:13,640 --> 00:43:14,881
Ming, let me manage your money.

1009
00:43:14,961 --> 00:43:16,200
Yitong has stood by you for years.

1010
00:43:16,200 --> 00:43:17,560
Now it is your turn to back her.

1011
00:43:17,680 --> 00:43:19,120
Ming, saving money is discipline.

1012
00:43:19,120 --> 00:43:20,720
It is your strongest safety net.

1013
00:43:20,720 --> 00:43:20,881
Ming.

1014
00:43:20,881 --> 00:43:21,560
Save what?

1015
00:43:21,841 --> 00:43:22,881
Text Yu Ming.

1016
00:43:23,120 --> 00:43:24,600
Send him all the photos you took.

1017
00:43:24,881 --> 00:43:26,281
Commit to the act.

1018
00:43:26,401 --> 00:43:27,680
Think long term.

1019
00:43:31,240 --> 00:43:31,801
That motorcycle behind us...

1020
00:43:31,881 --> 00:43:32,801
I noticed it long ago.

1021
00:43:33,120 --> 00:43:34,080
He is following us.

1022
00:43:34,520 --> 00:43:35,640
Speed up. Circle around.

1023
00:43:55,610 --> 00:44:02,620
♪The road ahead is still so long
Where have you gone?♪

1024
00:44:04,180 --> 00:44:11,340
♪Under the blazing sun
I keep heading north♪

1025
00:44:12,760 --> 00:44:20,220
♪To those who pass me by
You don't have to look at me♪

1026
00:44:21,360 --> 00:44:28,640
♪Just keep walking your own way
I'll manage on my own♪

1027
00:44:31,630 --> 00:44:35,230
♪Is the rain falling hard?♪

1028
00:44:35,870 --> 00:44:39,000
♪Is there someone
to hold an umbrella for you?♪

1029
00:44:40,160 --> 00:44:44,940
♪The wind has blown
the numbers off the signs♪

1030
00:44:44,940 --> 00:44:47,930
♪Where am I supposed to go?♪

1031
00:44:48,730 --> 00:44:52,250
♪Can I change my mind?♪

1032
00:44:53,010 --> 00:44:56,240
♪How do I go on without you?♪

1033
00:44:57,550 --> 00:45:02,080
♪When will this
endless rain finally stop?♪

1034
00:45:02,080 --> 00:45:04,780
♪Then I'll wait for you♪

1035
00:45:04,780 --> 00:45:08,780
♪Please don't leave me waiting♪

1036
00:45:23,060 --> 00:45:26,590
♪Is the rain falling hard?♪

1037
00:45:27,410 --> 00:45:30,750
♪Is there someone
to hold an umbrella for you?♪

1038
00:45:31,610 --> 00:45:36,450
♪The wind has blown
the numbers off the signs♪

1039
00:45:36,450 --> 00:45:39,730
♪Where am I supposed to go?♪

1040
00:45:40,200 --> 00:45:44,130
♪Can I change my mind?♪

1041
00:45:44,490 --> 00:45:47,800
♪How do I go on without you?♪

1042
00:45:49,000 --> 00:45:53,430
♪When will this
endless rain finally stop?♪

1043
00:45:53,430 --> 00:45:56,190
♪Then I'll wait for you♪

1044
00:45:56,190 --> 00:46:00,040
♪Please don't leave me waiting♪
